title: An interactive room modeling system for 3D video
title_en: An interactive room modeling system for 3D video
abstract: 本研究は3Dビデオ向けのインタラクティブな室内モデリングシステムを扱っている。本研究は視点合成やカメラ制御のために室内空間を正確に再構築することを目的とし、複数ビューの射影行列から対応点を用いた幾何学的三角測量で三次元位置を復元する実装を提示している。本研究は奥行5m×幅5m×高さ2.8mの室内環境で複数台のカメラ（文献上は7台）を用いた評価を行い、室内再構築性能を検証した。
abstract_en: This work addresses an interactive room modeling system for 3D video. This work aims to reconstruct indoor spaces accurately for view synthesis and camera control by recovering 3D positions using geometric triangulation from multiple-view projection matrices and image correspondences. This work evaluated the approach in an indoor environment of 5m by 5m by 2.8m using multiple cameras (reported as seven cameras) to verify indoor reconstruction performance.
positioning_summary: 本研究は3Dビデオにおける室内スケールでの対話的な部屋モデル構築を扱う点で既存手法と異なる立場を取っている。 本研究は既存の背景モデリングやイメージベースの手法がカバーしにくい室内スケールの対話的構築というギャップを埋めることを目的としており、3Dビデオ制作者やカメラ制御用途を想定している。
positioning_summary_en: This work positions itself as an approach for interactive room-scale modeling for 3D video, distinguishing it from existing methods. This work aims to fill the gap of interactive room-scale modeling that is not well covered by prior background modeling and image-based techniques, targeting 3D video creators and camera-control applications.
purpose_summary: 本研究の目的は視点合成やカメラ制御に利用可能な高精度な室内モデルを対話的に構築することである。 本研究は室内スケールでの対話的モデリングを実現することを目標としており、3Dビデオ制作者やカメラ制御が必要な用途を対象にしている。
purpose_summary_en: The purpose of this work is to interactively build accurate indoor models that can be used for view synthesis and camera control. The purpose of this work is to realize interactive room-scale modeling aimed at 3D video creators and camera-control applications.
method_summary: 本システムは複数ビューの射影行列を用いて画像上の対応点(u1,v1),(u2,v2)から同次座標w(x,y,z,1)^Tを導出する線形方程式を構成して三次元位置を復元する方法を採用している。 本システムは係数行列Bの擬似逆B+を用いた幾何学的三角測量を主要な実装としており、複数カメラ映像から室内の三次元位置を復元する具体的な仕組みを持っている。
method_summary_en: The system constructs linear equations from multiple-view projection matrices using image correspondences (u1,v1),(u2,v2) to derive homogeneous coordinates w(x,y,z,1)^T and recover 3D positions. The system implements geometric triangulation using the pseudoinverse B+ of the coefficient matrix B as the main mechanism to reconstruct 3D positions in an indoor environment from multiple camera images.
evaluation_summary: 本研究は奥行5m×幅5m×高さ2.8mの室内空間を実験環境として複数台（文献上は7台）のカメラを用いて評価方法を実施した。 本研究は評価の結果として撮影構成における室内再構築が可能であることを示し、複数カメラでの室内再構築性能を確認した。
evaluation_summary_en: This work evaluated the approach in an experimental indoor environment of 5m by 5m by 2.8m using multiple cameras (reported as seven cameras) as the evaluation methodology. This work reported that the evaluation demonstrated feasible indoor reconstruction in the given capture configuration and confirmed reconstruction performance with multiple cameras.

Title: An interactive room modeling system for 3D video
Authors: Aya Isshiki, Ryuki Sakamoto, Hangsung Kim, Tomoji Toriyama, Kiyoshi Kogure, Itaru Kitahara
Year: 2007
Abstract: This work addresses an interactive room modeling system for 3D video. This work aims to reconstruct indoor spaces accurately for view synthesis and camera control by recovering 3D positions using geometric triangulation from multiple-view projection matrices and image correspondences. This work evaluated the approach in an indoor environment of 5m by 5m by 2.8m using multiple cameras (reported as seven cameras) to verify indoor reconstruction performance.
Positioning Summary: This work positions itself as an approach for interactive room-scale modeling for 3D video, distinguishing it from existing methods. This work aims to fill the gap of interactive room-scale modeling that is not well covered by prior background modeling and image-based techniques, targeting 3D video creators and camera-control applications.
Purpose Summary: The purpose of this work is to interactively build accurate indoor models that can be used for view synthesis and camera control. The purpose of this work is to realize interactive room-scale modeling aimed at 3D video creators and camera-control applications.
Method Summary: The system constructs linear equations from multiple-view projection matrices using image correspondences (u1,v1),(u2,v2) to derive homogeneous coordinates w(x,y,z,1)^T and recover 3D positions. The system implements geometric triangulation using the pseudoinverse B+ of the coefficient matrix B as the main mechanism to reconstruct 3D positions in an indoor environment from multiple camera images.
Evaluation Summary: This work evaluated the approach in an experimental indoor environment of 5m by 5m by 2.8m using multiple cameras (reported as seven cameras) as the evaluation methodology. This work reported that the evaluation demonstrated feasible indoor reconstruction in the given capture configuration and confirmed reconstruction performance with multiple cameras.
